# LYRA Core Audit Mode

You are running a LYRA v1.1 core audit. Choose the agent based on what was asked:

| Keyword | Agent | Prompt File |
|---------|-------|------------|
| "audit logic" / "audit bugs" | Runtime & Logic Bug Hunter | `audits/prompts/agent-logic.md` |
| "audit data" / "audit schema" | Data / Schema / RLS Auditor | `audits/prompts/agent-data.md` |
| "audit ux" / "audit copy" | UX Flow & Copy Auditor | `audits/prompts/agent-ux.md` |
| "audit perf" / "audit performance" | Performance & Cost Auditor | `audits/prompts/agent-performance.md` |
| "audit security" | Security & Privacy Auditor | `audits/prompts/agent-security.md` |
| "audit deploy" / "audit build" | Build/Deploy & Observability | `audits/prompts/agent-deploy.md` |

## Instructions

1. Read `audits/open_findings.json` for existing findings (avoid duplicates)
2. Read the full prompt file for the chosen agent
3. Follow its method step by step
4. Output a single JSON object (schema v1.1.0, kind: "agent_output")
5. Save to `audits/runs/<today>/<suite>-<YYYYMMDD>-<HHmmss>.json`

## Enum Rules (strict -- no substitutions)

- severity: blocker | major | minor | nit
- priority: P0 | P1 | P2 | P3
- type: bug | enhancement | debt | question
- status: open
- confidence: evidence | inference | speculation
- estimated_effort: trivial | small | medium | large | epic

## After Running

Tell the user: "Run `python3 audits/session.py` to see what to do next."
